  "text": "## Kubernetes RBAC ClusterRole Privilege Escalation Validation\n\nThis audit identifies all Go source files in kubernetes/kubernetes that validate RBAC ClusterRole escalation rules and prevent privilege escalation.\n\n### Core Escalation Check Functions\n\nThe primary escalation validation logic is implemented in `pkg/registry/rbac/escalation_check.go` with three key functions:\n\n1. **EscalationAllowed()** (line 32): Checks if a user belongs to the `system:masters` group, which is a superuser group with unrestricted permissions. This function performs early authorization bypass for privileged loopback connections.\n\n2. **RoleEscalationAuthorized()** (line 55): Validates whether a user is explicitly authorized to escalate the role resource they're attempting to modify. This function:\n   - Extracts the user from context\n   - Creates an authorization request with the special \"escalate\" verb (line 81)\n   - Checks against ClusterRoles and Roles (line 49-52)\n   - Returns true only if the authorizer decision is DecisionAllow\n\n3. **BindingAuthorized()** (line 101): Validates whether a user can bind a specific role by checking if they have the \"bind\" verb on that role. This is used for RoleBinding and ClusterRoleBinding creation/updates.\n\n### No-Escalation Validation Functions\n\nThe validation of rule coverage is implemented in `pkg/registry/rbac/validation/rule.go`:\n\n**ConfirmNoEscalation()** (line 53): The core validation function that:\n- Retrieves all rules the user currently has via RulesFor()\n- Uses `validation.Covers()` from k8s.io/component-helpers to check if user rules cover the rules they're trying to grant\n- Returns an error if the user attempts to grant permissions they don't hold\n- Handles both complete and incomplete rule resolution gracefully\n\n**ConfirmNoEscalationInternal()** (in `pkg/registry/rbac/validation/internal_version_adapter.go` line 27): Adapter function that converts internal version PolicyRules to v1 PolicyRules before calling ConfirmNoEscalation().\n\n### Storage Layer Implementations\n\nThe escalation checks are enforced at the storage layer for all RBAC resources:\n\n**ClusterRole Storage** (`pkg/registry/rbac/clusterrole/policybased/storage.go`):\n- Create() method (line 73): Checks EscalationAllowed() or RoleEscalationAuthorized() first, then validates rules via ConfirmNoEscalationInternal()\n- Update() method (line 93): Similar checks, also validates aggregationRule permissions requiring full cluster-admin privileges\n- hasAggregationRule() helper (line 124): Checks if role uses aggregation rules\n\n**Role Storage** (`pkg/registry/rbac/role/policybased/storage.go`):\n- Create() method (line 67): Namespace-scoped version of ClusterRole checks\n- Update() method (line 80): Same validation pattern with garbage collection field detection\n\n**ClusterRoleBinding Storage** (`pkg/registry/rbac/clusterrolebinding/policybased/storage.go`):\n- Create() method (line 69): Checks BindingAuthorized() first (line 75), then ConfirmNoEscalation() on role rules\n- Update() method (line 94): Similar checks via WrapUpdatedObjectInfo\n\n**RoleBinding Storage** (`pkg/registry/rbac/rolebinding/policybased/storage.go`):\n- Create() method (line 70): Namespace-scoped binding validation\n- Update() method (line 102): Same pattern with namespace extraction\n\n### Supporting Functions\n\n**IsOnlyMutatingGCFields()** (`pkg/registry/rbac/helpers.go` line 29): Helper that skips escalation checks when only garbage collection fields (ownerReferences, finalizers) are being modified, allowing the system to clean up resources without re-validating escalation.\n\n**CompactRules()** (`pkg/registry/rbac/validation/policy_compact.go` line 34): Utility function used in error reporting to combine similar rules for more readable error messages when escalation is denied.\n\n**RuleAllows()** (`plugin/pkg/auth/authorizer/rbac/rbac.go` line 178): The core RBAC authorization check that uses VerbMatches() to validate that a rule allows a requested verb.\n\n### Escalation Verb\n\nThe key special verb is **\"escalate\"** which is checked in RoleEscalationAuthorized(). This verb is:\n- Used as an authorization check when attempting to create/update roles or clusterroles without system:masters privilege\n- Defined in the valid resource verbs list in staging/src/k8s.io/kubectl/pkg/cmd/create/create_role.go (line 60)\n- Validated by the RBAC authorizer through the standard RuleAllows() mechanism\n\n### Security Model\n\nThe privilege escalation prevention works through a multi-layered approach:\n\n1. **Superuser Bypass**: Users in system:masters group can always escalate (EscalationAllowed)\n2. **Explicit Escalate Authorization**: Users can escalate if they have \"escalate\" verb on the role resource (RoleEscalationAuthorized)\n3. **Binding Authorization**: Users can bind roles if they have \"bind\" verb (BindingAuthorized)\n4. **Rule Coverage Validation**: Non-privileged users can only grant rules that are a subset of their current permissions (ConfirmNoEscalation)\n\nThis ensures that RBAC changes enforce the fundamental security principle that users cannot grant more permissions than they themselves possess.\n"
}

